[semihtml][title]Staff[/title]
The following is a current list of <strong>official Lovinity Community+ staff</strong>. These individuals put in volunteer hours to help this community run efficiently. Please don&#39;t hesitate to talk to any of them. However, we highly recommend using our support tickets system (About -&gt; Support Tickets , or email support@lovinity.org ) opposed to directly messaging a staff for staff related matters. That way, you will get a response faster and more efficiently.

<h2>Administrators</h2>
Administrators (and advisers) are the <strong>highest level of staff</strong>. They operate the website and its procedures as well as help out in any of the other teams that need the help.<br />
<br />
[block display_mode="boxes" must_have_avatar="0" must_have_photo="0" include_form="0" usergroup="2" max="30" start="0" pagination="0" defer="1" sort="random ASC"]main_members[/block]
<h2>Advisers</h2>
Advisers are also on the same level as administrators. Advisers are <strong>professionals</strong> whose focus is in psychology, sociology, social work, LGBTQA+ affairs, activism, or other related fields. They provide guidance for website staff when needed and are a check on power for administrators.<br />
Though advisers are on the same level as administrators, they do not run the website and are usually only around when assistance is needed. Therefore, please do not approach advisers for staff matters.<br />
<br />
