<h2>Moderators</h2>
Moderators are the staff that <strong>go through content submitted on the website</strong>. They make sure everything is appropriate and in line with the website&#39;s rules and policies. Should something not be in line, moderators will take appropriate action to ensure the problem is corrected.<br />
<br />
[block display_mode="boxes" must_have_avatar="0" must_have_photo="0" include_form="0" usergroup="3" max="30" start="0" pagination="0" sort="random ASC" defer="1"]main_members[/block]
<h2>Developers</h2>
Developers <strong>work on the back end of the website</strong>. They do the coding and technical work to make sure the website is functioning properly. They also code in new features as needed.

<h2>Ambassadors</h2>
Ambassadors are in charge of <strong>relations outside of the website</strong>. They coordinate affiliations with other websites and conduct business relating to outside sources. They also help plan website and community events.

<h2>Mentors</h2>
Although anyone is free to give advice and support to members in the community, mentors are those chosen by staff to be the most helpful and trustworthy individuals when it comes to <strong>help and support</strong>. If you need someone to talk to, mentors will be there for you.<br />
